{
  "benchmark": "stage19-wld-range2-black-fairness-benchmark",
  "description": "Benchmark for adopting the full +2 root-only WLD pre-exact window so that black-to-move parity positions also receive an exact WLD solve before the exact endgame boundary. The expert-like 14-empty set is exact-referenced; the impossible 18-empty holdout checks black parity cost and completion behavior.",
  "adoptionDecision": {
    "adopted": true,
    "adoptedWldPreExactEmpties": 2,
    "defaultActivationRule": "Automatically enable wldPreExactEmpties=2 when maxDepth >= 8 and timeLimitMs >= 3000; otherwise default to 0.",
    "notes": [
      "The 14-empty exact-reference set showed perfect outcome agreement for +2 WLD and the same move-agreement count as the baseline depth-limited search.",
      "The 18-empty black holdout confirmed that the +2 window finally reaches the black-to-move parity bucket, although some heavy loss proofs can still time out and fall back heuristically.",
      "Future technique experiments should be benchmarked separately on exact and WLD buckets, because the useful range and runtime trade-offs differ substantially."
    ]
  },
